# Domain Name System (DNS)

## What is DNS?

DNS translates domain names into IP addresses.

Example:

google.com

↓

142.250.x.x

## Why DNS is Needed

Humans can easily remember names but computers communicate using IP addresses.

## DNS Resolution Process

1. User enters a domain name.
2. Browser checks local cache.
3. DNS query is sent.
4. DNS server returns the IP address.
5. Browser connects to the destination server.

## Common DNS Record Types

### A Record
Maps a domain name to an IPv4 address.

### AAAA Record
Maps a domain name to an IPv6 address.

### MX Record
Used for email servers.

### CNAME Record
Creates aliases for domain names.

## Key Learning

DNS acts as the Internet's phonebook and is one of the first services involved when accessing a website.

